<TEXT>
<P>
 After spending the first month of the new TV season on top of the ratings, 
ABC's "Home Improvement" fell to second last week, edged out by the show that 
follows it on Tuesday nights, "Grace Under Fire." 
</P>
<P>
 "Grace Under Fire," which stars Brett Butler, was seen in about 19.5 million 
homes, according to figures released Tuesday by the A.C. Nielsen Co. 
</P>
<P>
 ABC had four other shows in the Top 10 but wound up in a tie with CBS for the 
weekly lead, with NBC in third despite its new hospital drama 'ER" finishing 
No. 3 for the week. The only other first-year series to crack the Top 20 was 
NBC's "Madman of the People." 
</P>
<P>
 The most dramatic element in the weekly ratings was that only one network 
newsmagazine finished in the Top 20: CBS' venerable "60 Minutes," at No. 5. 
ABC's once-mighty "PrimeTime Live," pitted last Thursday against "ER" and "Eye 
to Eye," finished 87th among the week's 96 prime-time network programs. 
