<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING BRIEFING: DESPITE WYCHE'S TOUGH TALK, BUCCANEERS STILL FEATHERWEIGHTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAL FLORENCE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After the Tampa Bay Buccaneers lost, 41-16, to the San Francisco 49ers on 
Sunday at Candlestick Park, Coach Sam Wyche said of his team's aggressive style 
of play:  
</P>
<P>
 "We didn't come here to play courtesy football. At least we wanted to 
establish toughness, that we were a mean . . . nasty football team." 
</P>
<P>
 Comment from C.W. Nevius of the San Francisco Chronicle: "Here's a suggestion. 
If you want to look mean, why don't you start by taking that plumed fop with 
the pencil-thin mustache off the side of your helmet? 
</P>
<P>
 "It's hard to scare anybody when the side of your head looks like Louis XIV." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Trivia time: Which college football stadium has the largest seating capacity? 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Different view: Larry Guest of the Orlando Sentinel in Florida recalls that 
former Washington Redskin quarterback Sonny Jurgensen used to throw annual 
back-yard parties for his offensive linemen. 
</P>
<P>
 One year the linemen asked Sonny's 5-year-old son, Hans, if he knew what his 
dad's jersey number was. It was 9 but he said 6 and was teased about it. 
</P>
<P>
 Sonny retorted, "That's because, thanks to you goons, every time he sees me 
I'm upside down." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Collector's item: Woody Woodburn of the Ventura Star-Free Press writes that 
regardless of how well Michael Jordan plays for the Scottsdale Scorpions of the 
Arizona Fall League, he's a bargain, considering he gets only $16 a day in meal 
money. 
</P>
<P>
 "I mean, his endorsement on the back of a check is worth about three times 
that." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Selective memory: Fritz Shurmur, a former Ram defensive coordinator who now 
holds the same position with the Green Bay Packers, on defensive end Reggie 
White: 
</P>
<P>
 "I know there is no one in the league playing at his level right now, and I 
doubt that anyone ever has." 
</P>
<P>
 Hey, Fritz, ever hear of Deacon Jones, the Rams' Hall of Fame defensive end 
who had an estimated 180 quarterback sacks before the statistic became official 
in 1982? 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Is it worth it? More on the llamas used as caddies at a golf course in 
Horsham, Pa. 
</P>
<P>
 Their use requires a foursome because the animals must carry two bags apiece 
for balance and walk the course in pairs to ensure that the animals behave.  
</P>
<P>
 A handler must also go along to keep them from wandering away. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Say what? Greg Hansen of the Arizona Daily Star commenting on Arizona's game 
with Oregon on Saturday at Eugene, Ore.: 
</P>
<P>
 "It will be the biggest game in Oregon history, without question." 
</P>
<P>
 Is it possible that Hansen forgot about Oregon's Rose Bowl game with Ohio 
State in 1958? 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Looking back: On this day in 1969, the Oakland Raiders beat the San Diego 
Chargers, 24-12, tying the AFL record for consecutive regular-season games 
without a loss at 15. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Trivia answer: Michigan Stadium at the University of Michigan with a seating 
capacity of 102,501. 
</P>
