 Quarterback Brett Favre, forced out of last Thursday's game against Minnesota 
because of a muscle tear in his side, said that he expects to play against 
Chicago on Monday night. . . . Offensive tackle Mike Kenn underwent his second 
magnetic resonance imaging exam in two days for a back problem that could cut 
short his 17th and final season with the Atlanta Falcons. Kenn, 38, underwent 
an MRI exam Monday in a bid to find the problem, believed to be protruding 
disks. Physicians will compare the two tests in an effort to make a precise 
diagnosis, said Falcon spokesman Frank Kleha. . . . Cincinnati signed free 
agent quarterbacks Erik Wilhelm and Todd Philcox, both former Bengals. They 
will back up Jeff Blake, who is expected to start Sunday against the Cowboys 
because of injuries to David Klingler, who has a sprained knee, and Don Hollas, 
who suffered a separated shoulder. . . . Texas officials are pursuing a 
drunken-driving investigation against injured Cowboy Erik Williams, who 
remained hospitalized after an automobile accident. 
