<TEXT>
<P>
 Catfish season is winding down, but what a way to go. 
</P>
<P>
 Le Hai of Westminster set an Irvine Lake record with a 61-pound 8-ounce 
catfish under a full moon last Saturday. And then Bon Seng, also of 
Westminster, landed one at 58-8 -- from the same boat. 
</P>
<P>
 Hai's fish might also be a state record for channel catfish. A biologist from 
the Department of Fish and Game will determine whether it is a channel or blue 
catfish today. Blue catfish grow considerably larger than channel catfish. 
</P>
