<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; USC; THEN THERE WERE FOUR FOR ROSE BOWL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Rose Bowl race: 
</P>
<P>
 -- If Arizona (4-0) wins the rest of its games, it goes to the Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 -- If Oregon (3-1) wins the rest of its games -- it plays Arizona on Saturday 
-- and if Washington State loses another game, the Ducks go to the Rose Bowl. 
</P>
<P>
 -- If USC (4-1) wins the rest of its games -- the Trojans will play Arizona on 
Nov. 12 -- and someone else beats Oregon, the Trojans go to the Rose Bowl.  
</P>
<P>
 -- If Washington State (3-1) wins the rest of its games and if Arizona loses 
twice, the Cougars go to the Rose Bowl.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Washington State will play at Cal on Saturday before USC plays at Pullman on 
Nov. 5. The Cougars lead the Pac-10 in total defense by a wide margin, giving 
up 214.6 yards per game, compared to runner-up Arizona's 263.7. Washington 
State leads the Pac-10 in every major defensive category and leads the nation 
in rushing defense with a 53-yard average. Before their 28-21 victory over 
Arizona State last weekend, the Cougars hadn't given up more than 10 points in 
a game. EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
