<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: HACIENDA HEIGHTS; 
4-YEAR-OLD GIRL FALLS UNDER BUS TIRES, IS KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 4-year-old girl was run over and killed by a Foothill Transit bus in 
Hacienda Heights on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 3:45 p.m. at Hacienda Boulevard and La Subida 
Drive, according to California Highway Patrol Sgt. Bruce Bonnett. He said the 
child, identified as Lorraine Hayes of Hacienda Heights, fell under the tires 
as she and her mother were getting off the bus and the driver was beginning to 
pull away. The child died at the scene, Bonnett said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
