</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pam Prine 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress, Sophomore 
</P>
<P>
 Soccer/Defender 
</P>
<P>
 Prine, from Troy High, is a key contributor to Cypress' outstanding defense, 
but she also has a vital role in the offense. She and her teammates have yet to 
allow a goal in 11 games this season.In that time, Cypress had outscored 
opponents, 54-0. Prine scored two goals and had two assists as Cypress beat San 
Diego City, 8-0, and San Diego Mesa, 2-0. Prine is tied for the team lead in 
goals with Traci Osman. Each has seven. 
</P>
