<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP; REGALS CLAIMS 1ST VOLLEYBALL SCIAC TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran swept Whittier, 15-5, 15-6, 15-8, on Tuesday night at Whittier, 
clinching its first Southern California Intercollegiate Athletic Conference 
women's volleyball title. 
</P>
<P>
 The last volleyball championship of any kind for the Regals was an NAIA 
District 3 title in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
 Kelli McCaskill had eight kills and Liz Martinez had 14 assists to lead Cal 
Lutheran (18-7, 10-0). 
</P>
<P>
 WOMEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 1, Southern California College 0 -- Amy Lewis scored in the 30th 
minute as the Mustangs (4-11-1) won a nonconference match in Newhall. 
</P>
<P>
 Kariss Steinert had 10 saves to record her second shutout. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark 1, Santa Barbara City 1 -- Heather Heit scored in the 75th minute to 
salvage a tie in the Western State Conference match at Santa Barbara. Heit, a 
midfielder, hit a free kick just under the crossbar from about 20 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark (6-2-1, 5-1-1) fell behind when Santa Barbara (5-0-2 in conference 
play) scored 17 seconds into the second half. 
</P>
<P>
 MEN'S SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
 The Master's 3, Concordia 0 -- Stephen Janho scored two goals to lead the 
Mustangs (14-2-1) in a nonconference match at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 Lucas Principe scored the first goal for Master's, which has won three in a 
row and 11 of 12. Kris Bage had three saves. 
</P>
<P>
 GIRLS' VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Royal d. Simi Valley, 15-8, 15-5, 15-8 -- Kelly Ahern had 13 kills and Jessica 
Cruz added nine for the Highlanders (9-6, 7-4) in a Marmonte League match at 
Royal. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park d. Thousand Oaks, 15-7, 5-15, 15-5, 12-15, 15-13 -- Julie Wastell 
had 16 kills to lead the Panthers (11-2, 9-2) in a Marmonte League match. 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist d. Maranatha, 15-13, 10-15, 15-8, 15-5 -- Darcie Frazier had 22 
kills to lead the Knights (13-0, 6-0 in Alpha League play) to victory in a 
showdown for first place at L.A. Baptist. 
</P>
<P>
 GIRLS' TENNIS 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake 12, Agoura 6 -- Helena Horak swept her matches as the No. 1 singles 
player for Westlake (12-3, 9-2) in a Marmonte League match. Agoura is 12-4 and 
8-3. 
</P>
<P>
 BOYS' CROSS-COUNTRY 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 22, Camarillo 33; Thousand Oaks 15, Westlake 49; Camarillo 15, 
Westlake 50 -- Eleazar Hernandez of Camarillo won the Marmonte League meet in 
14 minutes 59 seconds, but Thousand Oaks placed five runners among the first 
seven finishers to go 7-0 in league competition for the third season in a row. 
</P>
