<HEADLINE>
<P>
PREP ROUNDUP; MARINA GIRLS MOVE INTO THIRD-PLACE TIE IN LEAGUE VOLLEYBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Marina, led by Marcy Crouch's 27 kills, moved into a third-place tie with 
Esperanza in Sunset League girls' volleyball by beating Fountain Valley, 10-15, 
17-15, 15-6, 15-12, Tuesday at Fountain Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Marina (8-7, 3-4) took an 11-4 lead in Game 4 but had to hold off Fountain 
Valley.The Barons scored eight of the next nine points to tie the score, 12-12, 
but Jessica Lyon served an ace and Crouch had two kills to end the match. 
</P>
<P>
 "The last game we got up a little bit and started pressing ourselves," Marina 
Coach Jason Bilbruck said. "In the timeout, I told Marcy, 'You're the one we 
need to win this one.' " 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley (4-6, 2-5) was led by Kristin Moro, who had 20 kills, 
including six in the first game, when Marina made several unforced errors. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Vikings' play improved in the second game, which had four lead 
changes. At 15-15, a double-hit was called on Fountain Valley, and on the next 
point, Moro's kill attempt was wide, giving Marina the game. GABE LACQUES 
</P>
</TEXT>
