<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ANAHEIM; GUNMAN SOUGHT AFTER MAN SLAIN, YOUTH HURT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THAO HUA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police are searching for a gunman who opened fire from a car, killing a man 
and wounding a teen-age boy. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers responding to reports of gunfire in the 1800 block of Neighbors 
Avenue late Monday found John Ernest Garcia, 25, of Anaheim sprawled near an 
apartment building, Police Sgt. Charles Chavez said Tuesday.Paramedics 
pronounced him dead at the scene of a chest wound. 
</P>
<P>
 A 17-year-old male who was shot in the hip was taken to the Anaheim Memorial 
Hospital by friends before police arrived, Chavez said. The youth, whose 
identity was not made public, was later transferred to UCI Medical Center in 
Orange. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators believe Garcia and the teen-ager were standing near the curb 
when a car stopped in front of them, Chavez said. An argument ensued and 
someone in the car opened fire about 10 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 "It appeared that (Garcia) staggered a few steps before he fell," Chavez said. 
</P>
<P>
 Descriptions of the assailant, who was last seen heading east on Neighbors 
Avenue, remained sketchy as police continued searching the neighborhood for 
witnesses. Nobody had been found who saw what happened, except the teen-ager. 
"And he's not telling much," Chavez said. "In all honesty, we're puzzled as far 
as motive." 
</P>
<P>
 There was no evidence of a gang-related crime, Chavez said. THAO HUA 
</P>
</TEXT>
