COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; SCHOOL REOPENING CELEBRATION TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 500 residents, community leaders and school personnel will celebrate the 
reopening of Neomia B. Willmore Elementary School in a ceremony tonight, a 
district spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 10-acre campus was closed several years ago as a result of school boundary 
changes, and leased to a court-reporting school.Earlier this year, the 
Westminster School District Board of Trustees voted unanimously to reopen the 
site in September to accommodate about 540 children who live within walking 
distance and who had been bused to other schools, said spokeswoman Audrey 
Brown. 
</P>
<P>
 The district has spent $1.5 million to renovate the building and campus with 
new roofing, floors, fencing, carpeting, asphalt and irrigation systems, Brown 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The celebration, which is open to the public, will be held at the campus, 7122 
Maple St., at 6 p.m. Festivities will include multicultural performances, 
refreshments and a tribute to Neomia Willmore, former district trustee for whom 
the school as named. JON NALICK 
</P>
