<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: CARSON TO REPRESENT CITIES ON LAFCO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura City Councilman Gregory L. Carson has been appointed a city 
representative to the Local Agency Formation Commission, a state planning 
agency that oversees annexation issues, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 LAFCO has two regular city representatives and one alternate. Carson has 
served as the alternate for the last six months, and will now become a regular 
representative with the retirement of Thousand Oaks Mayor Alex Fiore. 
</P>
<P>
 The other regular city representative is Ojai City Councilman Robert McKinney. 
The new alternate is Moorpark City Councilman Bernardo Perez. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
