<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; OFFICIALS WARN OF ILLEGAL MEAT SALES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Concerned about reports that door-to-door solicitors are selling meat, poultry 
and fish illegally in Camarillo, Ventura County officials have warned that such 
products may be substandard and cost more than regular market prices. 
</P>
<P>
 Bill Korth, director of the county's Weights and Measures Division, said 
street sales of meat are in violation of local and state laws. 
</P>
<P>
 "Attempts to sell meat, fish and poultry by the box or serving are illegal," 
Korth said.  
</P>
<P>
 "California law states that these items can only be sold by net weight. If 
they are selling in the Camarillo area, you can be sure they are active in all 
areas of the county." 
</P>
<P>
 Korth said that county residents are being advised not to confront the sellers 
but to report them to county officials, local police departments or city 
business license divisions.  
</P>
<P>
 For more information or to file a complaint, call 654-2444. J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
