<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA, OXNARD; 3 KILLED, 1 INJURED IN SEPARATE 
ACCIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three men were killed and another was injured in two car accidents that took 
place in Ventura and Oxnard, authorities said Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Ventura crash, which occurred about 11:30 p.m. Monday, 22-year-old 
Eduardo Juevara Carbajal of Ojai died at the scene after the vehicle in which 
he was riding smashed into a tree, said Claude Ball, an officer with the 
California Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
 A second passenger died early Tuesday at Ventura County Medical Center, Ball 
said. As of late Tuesday, the coroner's office had not released the name of the 
second victim because they had been unable to notify his family.  
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the car, 21-year-old Juan C. Garcia of Ojai, suffered minor 
injuries and was taken to Ventura County Medical Center, where he was in fair 
condition.  
</P>
<P>
 According to authorities, two CHP officers spotted Garcia driving 65 to 70 
m.p.h. north on Ventura Avenue north of Dakota Street and just outside Ventura 
city limits, Ball said.  
</P>
<P>
 When the officers, who were driving south on Ventura Avenue, turned to follow 
Garcia's car, they saw the vehicle strike a palm tree and bounce back to the 
road, Ball said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Oxnard accident, 71-year-old Calvin Kittleson died after his car was 
hit broadside by a pickup truck that ran a red light at the intersection of 
Vineyard Avenue and Ventura Road, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Kittleson, a Virginia resident who was visiting his son and daughter-in-law in 
Ventura, was pronounced dead shortly after arrival at St. John's Regional 
Medical Center, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the pickup truck, 18-year-old Michael Calderwood of Oxnard, did 
not suffer any injuries. He was arrested on suspicion of vehicular 
manslaughter, police said. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
