<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: TORRANCE; 2 AIR FORCE 
OFFICIALS TO SPEAK ON AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The current and former secretaries of the Air Force will speak about the 
aerospace industry in the South Bay on Oct. 27 in Torrance. 
</P>
<P>
 The Business Roundtable Luncheon, sponsored by the El Camino College 
Federation, will feature remarks from Air Force Secretary Sheila Widnall and 
former Secretary Edward E. (Pete) Aldridge Jr. 
</P>
<P>
 Aldridge, the president and chief executive officer of the nonprofit Aerospace 
Corp. in El Segundo, served as under-secretary and secretary of the Air Force 
during the Ronald Reagan Administration. 
</P>
<P>
 The luncheon is at noon at the Torrance Marriott Hotel. For more information, 
call (310) 660-3685. 
</P>
