BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Northrop Grumman Settles Suit for $53 Million: The Los Angeles-based aerospace 
concern paid the sum to computer maker Data General Corp. to settle a lawsuit 
alleging software copyright infringement and trade secret violations. The suit 
was filed six years ago against two divisions of Grumman Corp., which Northrop 
Corp. bought last spring. Data General, based in Westboro, Mass., said the 
settlement follows a ruling by the U.S. Court of Appeals in Boston affirming 
most of a verdict favoring Data General. 
</P>
