<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: SECURITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SEC Probes Conversion Companies: Beta Well Service Inc. said the Securities 
and Exchange Commission has launched the informal investigation into it, its 
former parent Conversion Industries of Pasadena and related companies. Beta 
Well said it learned of the probe in an SEC letter dated Friday.The letter says 
the investigation is part of the commission's routine program of enforcing 
securities laws and that Beta Well shouldn't construe that any violations have 
occurred. The SEC asked Beta Well to hand over documents related to the sale of 
its securities, its overseas activities, information regarding reserves it set 
aside for uncollectible accounts, data valuing its assets and other matters. 
The American Stock Exchange recently began proceedings to delist Beta Well and 
Conversion shares because of unspecified disclosure problems. 
</P>
</TEXT>
