<P>
COUNTY HOME RESALE PACE IS BRISK, THOUGH TOTAL DECLINES; HOUSING: MARKET WAS 
ESPECIALLY STRONG COMPARED TO THE SAME MONTH A YEAR AGO. NEIGHBORING COUNTIES 
SHOW SEPTEMBER INCREASES. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN O'DELL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County homes on the resale market moved at a rapid clip in September, 
but figures released Tuesday by the California Assn. of Realtors seemed to 
suggest just the opposite. 
</P>
<P>
 The Los Angeles-based trade group -- official record-keeper for single-family 
home resales in the state -- said September sales in Orange County were down 
10.6% from a year earlier. By comparison, the group reported, resales were up 
15.4% in Los Angeles County and 15.8% in Riverside and San Bernardino counties. 
</P>
<P>
 What the trade group didn't explain was that September, 1993, was one of the 
hottest months for resales in Orange County, with 29.6% more homes closing 
escrow than a year earlier. In Los Angeles County, sales were up a mere 2.5% 
from the same month of 1992. 
</P>
<P>
 Pat Neal, the Garden Grove realtor who heads the state trade association, said 
Tuesday that last month "was the second-best September for Orange County in the 
past five years," with September, 1993, of course, having been the best. 
</P>
<P>
 Other figures released Tuesday by the realtor group showed the average price 
of a single-family resale home in Orange County at $215,990 for September, down 
0.8% from a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 That put the cost of housing in Orange County in fourth place in the state, 
behind the San Francisco Bay Area ($256,350), Santa Clara County ($251,610) and 
Monterey County ($221,690). Mixed Message 
</P>
<P>
 September's single-family home resales in Orange County declined 10.6% from 
the same month last year. The median price also dipped a bit, but less than 1%. 
Price and sales activity changes are from September, 1993: 04,26,10,08,08 
Median Price Sales County price change change Los Angeles $187,270 -4.7% 15.4% 
Orange 215,990 -0.8 -10.6 Riverside/San Bernardino 128,710 -3.0 15.8 San Diego 
174,620 0.8 -6.6 Statewide $181,750 -2.0 -1.8 Source: California Assn. of 
Realtors 
</P>
