<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Viratek Inc.: The Costa Mesa drug development company reported a third-quarter 
profit of $263,000, or 1 cent a share.That was 6% higher than earnings of 
$249,000, or 1 cent a share, for the same period last year. Revenue rose 25% to 
$2.5 million from $2 million. For the first nine months of the year, the 
company posted a loss of $1.1 million, or 6 cents a share, compared to a loss 
of $573,000, or 3 cents a share, for the same period last year. Nine-month 
revenue increased 50% to $6 million from $4 million. 
</P>
