<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: NEWPORT CORP.'S PROFIT SKYROCKETS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Newport Corp., an Irvine manufacturer of equipment for developing laser and 
optics technology, recorded a 78% increase in profit for the third quarter. 
Earnings came to $743,000, or 11 cents a share, up from a profit of $417,000, 
or 6 cents a share, for the same period a year earlier.Sales were up almost 10% 
to $21 million from $19.1 million. Year-to-date profit more than doubled to 
$2.3 million, or 33 cents a share, from $936,000, or 13 cents a share, for the 
first three quarters of 1993. The 1994 period included one-time gains totaling 
$745,000 from investment income in the second quarter and from the favorable 
settlement of a state tax audit in the first quarter. Nine-month sales were 
down 2% to $62.9 million from $64.3 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
